text: Adewole is a surname of Yoruba origin, meaning "the king/crown/royalty has entered the house (family)". Notable people with the name include: * Emmanuel Adewole (born 1990), Nigerian born, English footballer * Isaac Folorunso Adewole (born 1954), Nigerian professor of gynaecology and obstetrics * Tobi Adewole (born 1995), is an American soccer player == See also == * Adewale == References == Category:Yoruba-language surnames
title: Adewole
